  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop the<strong> dried cranberries</strong> finely</p><p>Peel<strong> </strong>and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lamb-koftas-and-herbed-spelt/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>spelt</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 15-20 min or until cooked through but with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return it to the pot</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lamb-koftas-and-herbed-spelt/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>lamb mince</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped cranberries</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and half of the <strong>sumac</strong> (you'll use the rest for garnish) with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Crumble in the <strong>beef</strong> <strong>stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>and mix very thoroughly until everything is combined (clean hands is the best way!)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lamb-koftas-and-herbed-spelt/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Divide the mixture into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span> and roll into balls – these are your <strong>koftas</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>koftas </strong>to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid a mess!) and put them in the oven for 12-15 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lamb-koftas-and-herbed-spelt/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, strip the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p><p>Trim and finely slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Dice the<strong> tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lamb-koftas-and-herbed-spelt/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Mix the <strong>Greek-style yoghurt</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lamb-koftas-and-herbed-spelt/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the spelt is cooked and drained, add the <strong>chopped mint</strong>,<strong> diced tomato</strong> and <strong>chopped spring onion</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Mix it all together – this is your <strong>herbed spelt</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lamb-koftas-and-herbed-spelt/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>yoghurt</strong> over the <strong>herbed spelt</strong> and top with the <strong>koftas</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the remaining <strong>sumac</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
